  "prompt": "How did you react when your parents didn't buy you a new mobile?",
  "response": "I understand that not getting something you want, like a new mobile phone, can be disappointing. While I don't have personal experiences or feelings, I can offer some suggestions on how you might handle the situation:\n\n1. **Express Your Feelings:** It's okay to feel upset or frustrated. Talk to your parents about how you feel and why having a new mobile is important to you.\n\n2. **Understand Their Perspective:** Try to see things from your parents' point of view. They might have reasons related to finances, responsibilities, or other priorities.\n\n3. **Find Alternatives:** Consider if there are other ways to achieve what you want. Maybe you can work towards earning the money to buy it yourself or agree on certain responsibilities to earn it.\n\n4. **Stay Positive:** Focus on the things you do have and find activities that make you happy without needing a new device.\n\n5. **Learn and Grow:** Use this opportunity to develop patience and understanding. It can also be a chance to enhance other skills or interests.\n\nRemember, open and honest communication with your parents can often lead to a better understanding on both sides.",
